subject: Mihai Banulescu
value:
@Mihai: We have had a lot of interactions, collisions, debates, defensive tendencies from both of our sides and I learned a lot from you in terms of how you think and how to better interact with you in general. I appreciate you letting me give you feedback and in turn giving me constant feedback and making me rethink how I thought about a lot of things. 

I want to work with you b/c I learn so much in terms of how to overcome my own feedback validations, how I value myself, what I let affect me and what leads to becoming a stronger emotionally and mentally person.

I would want to work with you more if you:
-allowed other trains of thought that may differ from your own
-were kinder in your feedback to people
-remembered your feedback and gave it after a discussion
-were able to follow discussions from people that may not be relevant to the discussion at hand
-put aside the differences you see in people an learned to still allow for free minded discourse 
-tried to unlearn your own biases towards me and how you valued me as a person
-any time I give you feedback I would prefer to not feel like whatever I said was not actually taken in and was just thrown back on me in a negative format. 
-analyzed why you did not trust me to perform certain actions however automatically believed that others you had not dealt with were able to perform those actions (ie lead a fun team, esp since I did not even want to lead a fun activity team lol) 

However I personally still know that I can do that if I wanted too based on my personal experience and I do not need to prove it to you.
